tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and high chloride. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glycosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), but no evidence of infection. HbA1c is unexpectedly low despite glycosuria, possibly due to anemia or recent changes in glucose control. Findings are consistent with renal dysfunction, possible tubular damage, and metabolic derangements; further nephrological and diabetic evaluation is recommended.
